f=Engineering/dev/custom/code-review-standards/SKILL.md · in=code-review-standards department's review discipline: change reviewed fixed order **integrity correctness security tests style** either approved returned specific, actionable requests. quality gate merge time, upstream quinn's release gate aegis's security pass. Integrity comes first because department authors agents, agent-authored code failure modes: *look* done without *being* done. · p=Reviews "look fine, ship it" bugs vulnerabilities enter. fixed-order checklist means load-bearing checks (does work, safe, tested) always happen before cosmetic ones, "request changes" names exact problem fix never "this feels off." · wu=Triggers: "review PR," "code review," "is mergeable," automatically change before reaches quinn's gate. · st:/ Protocol=`Load the change + the stack-profile's conventions — scope = THIS diff only \· -> 0 INTEGRITY (agent-authored code): real APIs? real data? tests intact? no stub-claimed-done? \· -> 1 CORRECTNESS: does it do what it claims? edge cases? error paths? \· -> 2 SECURITY: input validation, authz, secrets, injection surfaces (aegis pass if risky) \· -> 3 TESTS: coverage for the change, meaningful assertions, quinn's tiers satisfied` · in=**Integrity zero agent-code check.** authors agents, agent-authored code fails characteristic ways human-style review misses. Before anything else, check for: **fabricated APIs** (calls methods/endpoints/params don't exist verify against real dependency, diff's claim); **mock placeholder data left in** (hardcoded fixtures, `example.com`, lorem values presented wired-up); **weakened deleted tests** diff edits tests make gates pass automatic block pending justification); **stubs claimed done** (TODO/`NotImplemented`/empty handlers behind "feature complete" claim); **over-broad diffs** (changes files stated task doesn't require quality Rail 1-adjacent signal). Any integrity finding blocks before correctness even assessed. **Scope discipline.** Review what diff changes (plus immediate context). Pre-existing debt untouched code tech-debt-register entry (delivery-governance), review item reviews wander don't finish. **Correctness.** Trace happy path error paths; probe edge cases tests miss. beautiful, well-styled wrong answer still wrong (spark's rule, engineering edition). **Security.** Input validation, authorization checks, secret handling, injection/XSS/SSRF surfaces. Anything touching new external surface auth path routes aegis before approval. **Tests.** change carry tests? they assert behavior, run? quinn's required tiers change type exist? tests non-trivial logic request changes. **Style last.** stack-profile conventions, naming, readability real subordinate; never block correct, safe, tested change taste alone. **Charter gate.** diff introduces external-tool call, confirm plan-locked (Rail 1). touches data mutation, confirm routes through operator-run-script path (Rail agent-executed destructive diff automatic block. **Verdict.** APPROVE, REQUEST CHANGES item `file:line problem fix`. generic notes. · of=`## Review: [PR/change] \· Integrity: [pass / findings] \· Correctness: [pass / findings] \· Security: [pass / findings / →aegis] \· Tests: [pass / gaps] \· Style: [pass / notes] \· Charter: [external-tool calls plan-locked? \· DB writes routed to operator?] \·  \· ### Verdict: APPROVE / REQUEST CHANGES` · pr=**Fixed order: integrity correctness security tests style.** load-bearing checks never get skipped cosmetic ones., **Agent-authored code checked agent failure modes first** fabricated APIs, leftover mocks, weakened tests, stubs claimed done, over-broad diffs. "Looks done" "is done.", **Review diff, codebase** pre-existing debt goes register, verdict., **Every request actionable** `file:line problem fix`, never "feels off.", **Don't block correct+safe+tested work taste.**, **Charter breaches diff automatic blocks**, style notes., **Risky surfaces route aegis** reviewer isn't last word security. · f=stack-profile conventions review universal correctness/security/test grounds, flag missing conventions dev., Reviewer lacks domain context route owning agent (dana/raj/mia/nova) rather approve blind., Time pressure skip review refused; unreviewed merge charter/process breach, escalated. · b:with Other Skills=`architecture-decisions` sets decisions; enforces them PR., `delivery-governance` (sibling) defines what "done" "mergeable" mean process-wise; checks code itself., Downstream: **quinn** gates release (tiers regression Reticle); **aegis** owns deep security; first, per-change filter. · h2:Stack Notes (dated)=`assets/stack-notes-typescript-node-2026-07.md` TypeScript/JS/React conventions style correctness steps check. Applies stack-profile names TypeScript/Node; adopted marketplace (ECC) 2026-07-10; method conflicts resolve skill.